{
  "text": "Author Manuscript Published OnlineFirst on October 28, 2016; DOI: 10.1158/0008-5472. CAN-16-1656 revealed significant associations between HER2 staining and advancing stage and grade of disease and tumor recurrence with only 1 in 2,525 (0.04%) cases exhibiting HER2 gene amplification. It is also known that EGFR overexpression is associated with the development of CRPC in patients [CITATION_1] . However, EGFR expression is not significantly associated with tumor differentiation, positive margins, extra-prostatic invasion, or preoperative prostate-specific antigen (PSA) [CITATION_2] suggesting that EGFR expression only increases during disease progression and in the development of castration resistant disease.",
